==Models==
===Routley–Meyer models===
The standard model theory for relevance logics is the Routley-Meyer ternary-relational semantics developed by Richard Routley and Robert Meyer. A Routley–Meyer frame F for a propositional language is a quadruple (W,R,*,0), where W is a non-empty set, R is a ternary relation on W, and * is a function from W to W, and formula_31. A Routley-Meyer model M is a Routley-Meyer frame F together with a valuation, formula_32, that assigns a truth value to each atomic proposition relative to each point formula_33. There are some conditions placed on Routley-Meyer frames. Define formula_34 as formula_35.
